text: Teh tarik and chapatti were average. But the ghee thosai was excellent. The after lunch crowd made ordering easy and service was good.

My review is only for the indian rojak, which I usually eat at Indian muslim stalls and therefore I'm able to compare. The sauce is thick, lot of peanuts, not too sweet. I like it better than Sri Sun's. The variety of their Indian rojak is however, less than Sri Sun's.
Food is okay but there's no prices on the menu. I've eaten here a few times but I recently got overcharged which was quite clearly not a mistake.
